OL,3,CFarm animals were so malnourished they
OL,4,Cstarted trying to eat each other
OL,6,FChristian Jowett, prosecuting on
OL,7,Fbehalf of the council, told the court
OL,8,Fthat Richard Scarfe, who had previous
OL,9,Fconvictions under the Animal Welfare
OL,10,FAct 2006, had been banned from keeping
OL,11,Fanimals for a period of five years
OL,12,Ffrom January 25, 2022.
OL,14,FFrom that point the local authority
OL,15,Fwould visit the farm regularly to
OL,16,Fensure animals were being kept safely
OL,17,Fat the farm by Brogan Scarfe and to
OL,18,Fmake sure Richard Scarfe had no direct
OL,19,Finvolvement in their care.
