OL,6,FHywel Davies, for Richard Scarfe, said
OL,7,Fhis client had no intention to ever
OL,8,Fwork in the farming industry again. He
OL,9,Falso said the sheep and pigs were
OL,10,Fnever kept at the farm for commercial
OL,11,Freasons and the animals were being
OL,12,Fslaughtered only for consumption by
OL,13,Fthe Scarfe family.
OL,15,FMr Davies asked judge Catherine
OL,16,FRichards to take into account that
OL,17,FRichard Scarfe's wife relies on him
OL,18,Fentirely as does their son. He added
OL,19,Fthat his client had never been in
OL,20,Fcustody before and there were concerns
OL,21,Fwith how he would cope.
